<!--
  Link naming convention:
    os/base_link    - vehicle body (URDF root, driven by EKF odom→os/base_link TF)
    imu_xsens_link  - IMU sensor frame (matches imu_bridge.cpp frame_id)
    dvl_link        - DVL sensor frame (matches dvl_bridge.cpp frame_id)
    depth_link      - Depth sensor frame (matches pressure_sensor_bridge.cpp frame_id)

  Sensor joint rotations are zeroed: the sim bridges (imu_bridge, dvl_bridge,
  pressure_sensor_bridge) already perform NED/FRD→ENU/FLU conversion in C++.
  Adding CAD joint rotations here would double-rotate EKF inputs via TF.
  Only the translation offsets are kept from the original CAD export.

  Mesh package: tauv_autonomy/Osprey/meshes/
-->
